<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-03T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-03T13:00:00-05:00" n="309" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d309">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.114 Belgium/145a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-03T13:00:00-05:00">October 3,
                                    1935—1 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>69. Commander B. M. Thompson, a representative of the Treasury
                            Department, will visit Brussels in the near future to discuss question
                            of obtaining cooperation in preventing shipments of alcohol from Belgium
                            destined for smuggling into United States.</p>
                        <p>Please extend appropriate assistance and inform consular officers at
                            Antwerp and Rotterdam.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>